SSH on mac setup
https://flassari.is/2016/07/setup-ssh-keys-on-mac/
        Setup SSH keys on Mac
        Generate SSH keys, defaults at ~/.ssh/id_rsa and id_rsa.pub

        ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "your_email@example.com"
        Run Macâ€™s ssh-add command (not ssh-agent), adds default keys if no key is specifed, -K adds passphrases to keychain.

        ssh-add -K
        Create a text file called ~/.ssh/config with this content:

        Host *
        UseKeychain yes
        AddKeysToAgent yes
        IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_rsa

