How to SSH?

- make a private key on siteground dashboard
- save the passphrase!
- copy private key from siteground
- >>> touch ~/.ssh/[keyname.pem]
- >>> code ~/.ssh/[keyname.pem]
- paste, save (don't change linebreaks) called ~/.ssh/something.pem
- sudo chmod 600 something.pem
- ssh-add something.pem
- ssh-add -K something.pem (stores the passphrase in keychain...)
- ssh u185-hx3lgyl5ddtl@joon.be -p 18765

EXPORT PUBLIC KEY -> you need the passphrase!
- cd ~/.ssh
- ssh-keygen -y -f [keyname.pem] > [keyname.pub]

push files to server with RSYNC

you can use --dry-run to try out stuff!!

example:

rsync --rsh='ssh -p18765' --dry-run --delete-after --progress --archive "../htdocs/" "u185-hx3lgyl5ddtl@joon.be:~/www/joon.be/public_html/"
rsync [flags] [SRC] [DEST] 

you can also just pull everything down first!
